# Features and Use Cases

## Features
- Choose between Server Runtime, Local Host Runtime, and Client Runtime.
- Initialize server using a password and port.
- Log in using a username and password.
- Shut down server.
- Log out.
- Send messages.
- Receive messages.

## Brief Use Cases

### UC1 : Choose Server
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Host a chat group.

### UC2 : Choose Local Host
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Host and participate in a chat group.

### UC3 : Choose Client
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Participate in a chat group.

### UC4 : Start Server
- Primary Actor: Administrator
- Goal: Allow clients to connect.

### UC5 : Log In
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Join a server.

### UC6 : Shutdown Server
- Primary Actor: Adminstrator
- Goal: Close out chat group and disconnect clients.

### UC7 : Log Out
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Disconnect from server.

### UC8 : Send Message
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Talk to other users.

### UC9 : Receive Message
- Primary Actor: User
- Goal: Read what other users say.

## Use Case Traceability

|         Use Cases       | Feature(s) |
|-------------------------|------------|
| UC1 : Choose Server     | Feature 1  |
| UC2 : Choose Local Host | Feature 1  |
| UC3 : Choose Client     | Feature 1  |
